race.comment: Former Victorian HOT PURSUIT (5) is having her first run for the new yard but showed plenty of ability down south and should find this assignment to her liking. Tuned up for this with two recent trials and is sure to be right there at the business end. SINGULAR (9) will strip fitter second-up from the spell and gets in on the minimum weight. Include in calculations. The well-related TRAPASSI (1) (half to G1 winner Beiwacht) goes well for rider Kliese who has four wins and four placings from just 12 rides. Top-three commodity. MUTAFIQ (3) also hails from a handy family (half to 2xG3 winner Enthaar) and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. In the mix. NO LOVE LOST (6) makes some appeal.
